cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper proposes a framework for security event analysis in surveillance videos using convolutional neural network (CNN) framework. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with security and surveillance, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of real-time monitoring and object recognition suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of CNNs for object detection and recognition suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a novel framework for security event analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
